  "description": "A fairly advanced two-chamber smart refrigerator, presented on the market by the popular brand Samsung as part of the Grand+ line of devices. This model supports the SmartThings remote control system and the ability to integrate into a smart home system. The back wall of the refrigeration chamber is finished with a Metal Cooling insert, which smooths out minor temperature differences. The interior is arranged according to the SpaceMax principle - the device has an increased capacity (390 l), with fairly standard overall dimensions. The two-chamber Samsung Grand+ RB38C776CB1 refrigerator can additionally boast an Optimal Fresh+ section, which allows you to create a light freezing effect, which is useful for short-term storage of meat and fish raw materials in the refrigeration chamber, without deep freezing. There is an AI Energy energy consumption optimization system, with which, according to the manufacturer, you can achieve a 15 percent reduction in the load on the electrical network. Cooling and freezing chambers use separate cold distribution circuits, which prevents air flows from mixing. The device is based on an inverter compressor, the warranty period for the compressor system is 20 years.",
